August 28, 2012 Emanuel Jacobi  (emanuel.jacobi@desy.de)
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Release V01-04-01

- Modified I3EHEEventDigiest so that it fetches double
  neutrinoInteractionWeight instead of integer value. This is following
  the updates of juliet-interface functions to inject in-ice neutrinos
  with enhancment factor to the neutrino-nucleon cross section.
- Ophelia works in the split p-frame now. I3EHEFirstGuess reads
  split DOM map from p-frame instead of I3DOMLaunchSeriesMap.

  -- Shigeru Yoshida


June 25, 2012 Emanuel Jacobi  (emanuel.jacobi@desy.de)
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Release V01-04-00

Feature:

- Added a function to digest informations stored in the
  I3ParticleVect, the output from the millipede project.
- Added a function to display the energy loss profile
  of an event estimated by the millipede.
- Added the case to digest Juliet Neutrino primary
  events with the Millipede option

  -- Shigeru Yoshida

- Added converter from reco pulse to portia pulse and
  module to apply static (around brightest DOM)
  time window cleaning

  -- Aya Ishihara

- Remove reference to I3ConverterFactory

  -- Jakob van Santen

- Prevent crash by check if objects exists, otherwise
  pushing frame

  -- Keiichi Mase

- Remove dependecy on jebclasses.

  -- Emanuel Jacobi


